summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 11149, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the laying off, extending and establishing of Olympic Place, in the City of Seattle, as a public street and highway over and across portions of Block Three (3), Four (4), Eleven (11), Twelve (12), Thirteen (13)and Twenty-two (22), Northern Addition to the City of Seattle, and providing for the taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor, and for the ascertainment and payment of the just compensation to be made for the private property to be taken and damaged for said purpose, and for an assessment upon the property benefited for the purpose of making such compensation," approved on the 3rd day of August, 1904.
